<p>Carlotta Pavese, associate professor of philosophy at <a href="https://philosophy.cornell.edu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Cornell University</a>, will be moving to <a href="https://www.philosophy.ox.ac.uk/home" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Oxford University</a>, where she will be the Fulford Clarendon Professor in Philosophy of Mind and Cognitive Science and Fulford Fellow at St. Catherine&#8217;s College.<span id="more-54102"></span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-54106 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pavese-carlotta-photo1.jpg" alt="" width="446" height="297" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pavese-carlotta-photo1.jpg 446w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pavese-carlotta-photo1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pavese-carlotta-photo1-400x266.jpg 400w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 446px) 100vw, 446px" /></p>
<p>Professor Pavese works in philosophy of mind and cognitive science, philosophy of language, epistemology, action theory, and linguistics. You can learn more about her and her work <a href="https://www.carlottapavese.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a> and <a href="https://philpeople.org/profiles/carlotta-pavese" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p>
<p>She takes up her new positions at Oxford on September 1st, 2025.</p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2025/06/12/pavese-from-cornell-to-oxford/">Pavese from Cornell to Oxford</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>